-- FACTBOX: Global spending on research and development
-- 
-- Tue Nov 20, 2007 8:22pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/21/us-germany-science-factbox-idUSL1544645720071121

 

 (Reuters) - Germany, worried it is losing its reputation for scientific and technological prowess, is introducing policies to boost science and technology at its universities. 

 Below is a list of the most recent figures available from Eurostat on the proportion of gross domestic product a country spends on research and development. Most figures are for 2005. - Poland 0.57 percent - United Kingdom 1.76 percent - France 2.12 percent - Germany 2.49 percent - Sweden 3.89 percent - Switzerland 2.90 percent - United States 2.67 percent - Japan 3.20 percent (Compiled by Madeline Chambers)